LitCode 0.5.3 - Fixing a stupid mistake in the example

The example that is being used to demonstrate the power of literate programming is that of a program for
generating N prime numbers. And I made a stupid mistake: instead of testing for divisibility from 1 till N /
2, divisibility was being tested from 1 till (N / 2) - 1, which led to 4 also being considered as prime
number. This stupid mistake makes clear a very important thing: irrespective of the programming methodology
you have adopeted, stupid mistakes can always creep in.  
Embarrassed!